PhD Subject proposition
Network analysis through contextual data mining applied to the study and 
evolution of scientific communities.

_________________________________
Context
This PhD is in a joint project of the Laboratoire Hubert Curien in Jean 
Monnet University (http://laboratoirehubertcurien.fr)
 and the LIRIS lab at the INSA Lyon (http://liris.cnrs.fr/). It is 
subject of a
application for ANR (French national research fund) and a cooperative 
action within the Web Intelligence project
supported by the cluster ISLE of the Rhône Alpes region. The selected 
candidate will join of about 20 researchers working on data mining, 
information retrieval and knowledge modeling.

__________________________________
Candidate profile
Having a MSc or a Master in engineering degree in computer science at 
the end of the academic year 2008-2009,
skills in information retrieval, graph based representation network 
analysis would be appreciated. Good programming
capabilities are requested! An excellent level in English is also 
required. French is recommended but not
obligatory.

Starting date is 1 October 2009

Expressions of interest with a short CV should be sent by 1 June 2009 at 
the latest to :
Christine.Largeron@univ-st-etienne.fr
or
elod.egyed-zsigmond@insa-lyon.fr
__________________________________
Funding
The subject is likely to be funded by the cluster ISLE of the Rhône 
Alpes region
Amount: about 1700 euros gross monthly for 3 years
__________________________________
Some Links

-Some facts about Saint-Etienne can be found here:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint-Étienne.
-Saint Etienne is a medium size city with a quite low cost of living
(compared to same size cities in France).
-Paris can be reached from Saint Etienne in less than 3 hours via a direct
train. St. Etienne has a little Airport connected by RyanAir. The 
closest bigger airport is Lyon Saint Exupéry
(http://www.lyon.aeroport.fr).
-The city is surrounded by the "regional parc of pilat" in which almost
any outdoor activity can be practiced
(http://www.parc-naturel-pilat.fr/eng/).
-From a cultural point of view, the art museum in Saint-Etienne holds the
second national contemporary art collection, and classic concerts, dance
shows, and lyric operas are performed at the Saint-Etienne
"Massenet Opera" (http://www.decouvrez-le-votre.com/).
